                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I spoke of four articles—the dia<lb></lb>mond ring was among the things pawned—I let 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on that.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370612-name-274" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-274" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-274" type="surname" value="WELLESLY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-274" type="given" value="LADY"></interp>LADY WELLESLY</persName>
                  </hi>. I find all the five rings here—the two breast-pins, brooches, rings, two buttons and four watch-keys—they are all mine—every thing was in the room except the copper money. I know nothing of that.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370612-name-275" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-275" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-275" type="surname" value="STUBBINGS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-275" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM STUBBINGS</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> Five articles were pawned with me—the diamond ring was the fifth, (not the diamond and ruby ring.) I lent 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on it—I did not mean the diamond ring when I said they were worth no more than I lent on them—I look it for a paste ring.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I found them wrapped up in a towel together when I was on duty at the Duke of York's pillar.</p>
